Married murderers awaiting the death penalty for killing a teenage boy have been granted permission to have sex so their parents can have a grandchild to remember them by.

Jasvir Singh and his wife Sonia filed a petition asking for conjugal visits and the right to have children after they were given the death sentence following a lengthy public trial.

The couple kidnapped the 16-year-old son of a wealthy family and demanded a ransom - but when their scheme started to go wrong, they killed the boy to stop him identifying them.

